## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="f5127-102">System.Speech 的默认语义格式符合 W3C[语音识别 (SISR) 版本 1.0 的语义转译](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=201765)，其中的格式`tag`包含脚本的元素是`semantics/1.0`。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="f5127-102">The default semantic format for System.Speech conforms to the W3C [Semantic Interpretation for Speech Recognition (SISR) Version 1.0](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=201765), where the format for `tag` elements that contain script is `semantics/1.0`.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="f5127-103">必须指定的脚本<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsSemanticInterpretationTag>对象使用此格式。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="f5127-103">You must specify the script for <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsSemanticInterpretationTag> objects using this format.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="f5127-104">中的语法`semantics/1.0`:</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="f5127-104">In the syntax of `semantics/1.0`:</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="f5127-105">由"out"标识的包含规则元素的变量规则。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="f5127-105">The Rule Variable of the containing rule element is identified by "out".</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="f5127-106">"规则"以标识有权访问的规则元素包含的规则元素之外的变量规则的对象的名称。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="f5127-106">The name of the object that has access to the Rule Variable of rule elements outside the containing rule element is identified by "rules".</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="f5127-107">可以通过"rules.latest()"表示匹配查询文本的最新引用规则的结果。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="f5127-107">The result from the latest referenced rule that matches the utterance can be represented by "rules.latest()".</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="f5127-108">您还可以关联一个语义值与语法短语而无需使用脚本中，使用<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsNameValueTag>对象。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="f5127-108">You can also associate a semantic value with a phrase in a grammar without using script, using the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsNameValueTag> object.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="f5127-109">以下示例创建用于选择航班的城市的语法。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="f5127-109">The following example creates a grammar for choosing the cities for a flight.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="f5127-110">该示例使用<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsSemanticInterpretationTag>将语义值分配给每个城市，它是该市的机场代码。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="f5127-110">The example uses <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsSemanticInterpretationTag> to assign a semantic value to each city, which is the code for the city's airport.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="f5127-111">此示例还使用<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsSemanticInterpretationTag>分配所做的两个引用的每个单独的语义键<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRuleRef>名为对象`cityRef`到<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule>对象名为`cities`。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="f5127-111">The example also uses <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsSemanticInterpretationTag> to assign a separate semantic key for each of the two references made by the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRuleRef> object named `cityRef` to the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule> object named `cities`.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="f5127-112">语义键标识为出发城市或航班到达所在城市的已识别的城市。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="f5127-112">The semantic keys identify a recognized city as the departure city or the arrival city for the flight.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="f5127-113">处理程序<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.SpeechRecognized>事件使用的密钥来识别结果中检索语义。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="f5127-113">The handler for the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.SpeechRecognized> event uses the keys to retrieve the semantics from the recognition result.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="f5127-114">在代码示例中，"out"是指包含它的变量规则<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule>。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="f5127-114">In the code example, "out" refers to the Rule Variable of the containing <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule>.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="f5127-115">表达式"扩展。LeavingFrom"指的是命名的属性`LeavingFrom`的名为的规则上的变量规则`bookFlight`。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="f5127-115">The expression "out.LeavingFrom" refers to the property named `LeavingFrom` of the Rule Variable on the rule named `bookFlight`.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="f5127-116">表达式"rules.flightCities"是指在规则的变量规则其<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule.Id%2A>是`flightCities`，以及哪一个是规则引用的目标。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="f5127-116">The expression "rules.flightCities" refers to the Rule Variable on the rule whose <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule.Id%2A> is `flightCities`, and which is the target of a rule reference.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="f5127-117">在示例中，表达式"扩展。LeavingFrom=rules.flightCities;"将值分配规则从其<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule.Id%2A>是`flightCities`到名为属性`LeavingFrom`的名为的规则上的变量规则`bookFlight`。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="f5127-117">In the example, the expression "out.LeavingFrom=rules.flightCities;" assigns the value from the rule whose <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule.Id%2A> is `flightCities` to the property named `LeavingFrom` of the Rule Variable on the rule named `bookFlight`.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="f5127-118">请参阅[语义结果内容](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/622291af-615c-4a15-9014-2933aa3f89fe)，[语法规则名称引用](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/0777e975-8665-4cc3-957b-752743cb1bb9)，并[语法规则引用引用](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/dec3a809-9aa2-4139-893f-3a549ca1e03e)有关详细信息。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="f5127-118">See [Semantic Results Content](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/622291af-615c-4a15-9014-2933aa3f89fe), [Grammar Rule Name Referencing](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/0777e975-8665-4cc3-957b-752743cb1bb9), and [Grammar Rule Reference Referencing](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/dec3a809-9aa2-4139-893f-3a549ca1e03e) for more information.</span></span>  
  
```  
using System;  
using System.Speech.Recognition;  
using System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar;  
  
namespace SampleRecognition  
{  
  class Program  
  {  
    static void Main(string[] args)  
  
    // Initialize a SpeechRecognitionEngine object.  
    {  
      using (SpeechRecognitionEngine recognizer =  
         new SpeechRecognitionEngine(new System.Globalization.CultureInfo("en-US")))  
      {  
  
        // Create a rule for the cities, assign a semantic value to each city.  
        SrgsRule cities = new SrgsRule("flightCities");  
        SrgsItem chi = new SrgsItem("Chicago");  
        chi.Add(new SrgsSemanticInterpretationTag("out = \"ORD\";"));  
        SrgsItem bos = new SrgsItem("Boston");  
        bos.Add(new SrgsSemanticInterpretationTag("out = \"BOS\";"));  
        SrgsItem mia = new SrgsItem("Miami");  
        mia.Add(new SrgsSemanticInterpretationTag("out = \"MIA\";"));  
        SrgsItem dal = new SrgsItem("Dallas");  
        dal.Add(new SrgsSemanticInterpretationTag("out = \"DFW\";"));  
  
        SrgsOneOf airports = new SrgsOneOf(chi, bos, mia, dal);  
        cities.Add(airports);  
        cities.Scope = SrgsRuleScope.Private;  
  
        // Create a rule reference to the rule for cities.  
        SrgsRuleRef cityRef = new SrgsRuleRef(cities);  
  
        // Create the root rule for the grammar.  
        SrgsRule bookFlight = new SrgsRule("flightBooker");  
        bookFlight.Add(new SrgsItem("I want to fly from"));  
        bookFlight.Add(cityRef);  
        bookFlight.Add(new SrgsSemanticInterpretationTag("out.LeavingFrom=rules.flightCities;"));  
        bookFlight.Add(new SrgsItem("to"));  
        bookFlight.Add(cityRef);  
        bookFlight.Add(new SrgsSemanticInterpretationTag("out.GoingTo=rules.flightCities;"));  
        bookFlight.Scope = SrgsRuleScope.Public;  
  
        // Initialize the SrgsDocument, set the root rule, add rules to the collection.  
        SrgsDocument itinerary = new SrgsDocument(bookFlight);  
        itinerary.Rules.Add(cities);  
  
        // Create a Grammar object and load it to the recognizer.  
        Grammar g = new Grammar(itinerary);  
        g.Name = ("City Chooser");  
        recognizer.LoadGrammarAsync(g);  
  
        // Configure recognizer input.                  
        recognizer.SetInputToDefaultAudioDevice();  
  
        // Attach a handler for the SpeechRecognized event.  
        recognizer.SpeechRecognized +=  
          new EventHandler<SpeechRecognizedEventArgs>(recognizer_SpeechRecognized);  
  
        // Start recognition.  
        recognizer.RecognizeAsync();  
        Console.WriteLine("Starting asynchronous recognition...");  
  
        // Keep the console window open.  
        Console.ReadLine();  
      }  
    }  
  
    // Write to the console the text and the semantics from the recognition result.  
    static void recognizer_SpeechRecognized(object sender, SpeechRecognizedEventArgs e)  
    {  
      Console.WriteLine("Speech recognized: " + e.Result.Text);  
      Console.WriteLine();  
      Console.WriteLine("Semantic results:");  
      Console.WriteLine("  The departure city is: " + e.Result.Semantics["LeavingFrom"].Value);  
      Console.WriteLine("  The arrival city is: " + e.Result.Semantics["GoingTo"].Value);  
    }  
  }  
}  
  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="f5127-119">下面是语法的在上面的示例代码生成的 XML 格式。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="f5127-119">The following is the XML form of the grammar generated by the code in the example above.</span></span>  
  
```xml  
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>  
<grammar xml:lang="en-US" root="flightBooker" tag-format="semantics/1.0"   
version="1.0" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2001/06/grammar">  
  
  <rule id="flightBooker" scope="public">  
    <item> I want to fly from </item>  
    <ruleref uri="#flightCities" />   
    <tag> out.LeavingFrom=rules.flightCities; </tag>  
    <item> to </item>  
    <ruleref uri="#flightCities" />   
    <tag> out.GoingTo=rules.flightCities; </tag>  
  </rule>  
  
  <rule id="flightCities" scope="private">  
    <one-of>  
      <item> Chicago <tag> out="ORD"; </tag></item>  
      <item> Boston <tag> out="BOS"; </tag></item>  
      <item> Miami <tag> out="MIA"; </tag></item>  
      <item> Dallas <tag> out="DFW"; </tag></item>  
    </one-of>  
  </rule>  
  
</grammar>  
```
